Toryu
Reading, UK820 contributions
After years of going past it, to finally go in...
Aug 2023 ‚Ä¢ Family
That's right. For years on end, I've gone past this well known landmarks to Lisbon inhabitants, but never went in.
A bit of a mistake that I fortunately got to amend.
You enter and, while not bearing the full presence of a cathedral, the building does not disappoint, showcasing its own personality in the form of multiple altars to local saints (including Lisbon's patron saint, St. Anthony) and colourful stonework, all with the normal quiet of such a building.
If you're looking for some further experience, there are budget friendly tickets available to go atop the roof and even go into the building's dome (take care to not go on Sundays as the dome should be inaccessible due to Sunday mass). From here, you have a bit of a view of the surrounding neighborhood, while also being fairly close to the airport's South flight corridor. Just take care not to be up there when the full bell toll takes place (for example, Sunday at 11:50) as your ears will be at risk.
To get there, consider taking the n28 tram as it finishes its course right outside the main entrance.
Written August 23, 2023
